#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:25
msgid "## What is an operating system?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:27
msgid "Linux, UNIX, BSD, Windows, and MacOS are all **operating systems**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! abstract\n"
"    An operating system is a **set of programs that manages the available resources of a computer**.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:32
msgid "Among this management of resources, the operating system has to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:42
msgid "Manage the physical or virtual memory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  * '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:42
msgid ""
"The **physical memory** is made up of the RAM bars and the processor cache "
"memory, which is used for the execution of programs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  * '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:42
msgid ""
"The **virtual memory** is a location on the hard disk (the **swap** "
"partition) that allows the unloading of the physical memory and the saving "
"of the current state of the system during the electrical shutdown of the "
"computer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:42
msgid ""
"Intercept **access to peripherals**.  Software is rarely allowed to access "
"hardware directly (except for graphics cards for very specific needs)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:42
msgid ""
"Provide applications with proper **task management**.  The operating system "
"is responsible for scheduling processes to occupy the processor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:42
msgid "**Protect files** from unauthorized access."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:42
msgid "**Collecting information** about programs in use or in progress."
msgstr ""

